                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingEight">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed p-2" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-headingEight" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapseThree">
                                How do you manage approvals and stakeholders across Australia?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="flush-collapseEight" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="flush-headingEight" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                <ul>
                                    <li>
                                        We use lightweight governance. Weekly rituals, RACI notes, and decision logs keep everyone aligned. Stakeholders get concise updates, clickable prototypes, and clear next steps. When needed, we run design crits and playback sessions, so feedback is gathered efficiently and we avoid surprises late in the project. Decisions stay visible. Consistently.
                                    </li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
